 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.2.8","title":"task(opentui-import ingestion): Build side-effect and capability profile (IO, timers, env, platform assumptions)","description":"Objective: Detect non-UI side effects and capability assumptions that impact migration correctness (network calls, timers, file access, terminal APIs, env checks).\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n1. Capability profile is explicit and attached to component/effect origin.\\n2. Risk flags classify blocking vs warn-only assumptions.\\n3. Profile integrates with gap detector and certification risk sections.","notes":"Progress 2026-02-25: implemented effect-level capability inference + platform assumptions, project-level required/optional capability aggregation, risk flag classification (blocking vs warn-only), and migration_ir builder assumption plumbing; targeted tests passing via rch.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"VioletOak","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:37.770108194Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T04:39:48.413997376Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["analysis","capabilities","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.8","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:37.770108194Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.8","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:11.161450904Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.8","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:11.624085623Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","title":"task(opentui-import ingestion tests): Unit test suite for parser, graph, and semantic extractors","description":"Objective: Create broad unit coverage for intake, parser, module graph, state/effect extraction, style extraction, and capability profiling.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n1. Fixture matrix includes happy, edge, malformed, and adversarial cases.\\n2. Golden JSON snapshots verify deterministic extraction output.\\n3. Structured test logs include fixture ID, parser stage, and normalization hash.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:38.248815954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:20:05.904852991Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ingestion","opentui-import","test","unit"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T22:20:05.904768032Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:29:38.248815954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:12.083273446Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:12.548433556Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:13.011429242Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.2.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:13.642482734Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.3","title":"epic(opentui-import): Canonical IR and semantic normalization","description":"## Background\nNormalize extracted semantics into a canonical IR that captures intent independent of OpenTUI implementation details.\n\n## Scope\n- IR schema and invariants for state, interaction, layout, style, and effects.\n- Lowering + normalization passes with deterministic ordering/idempotence guarantees.\n- Intent graph inference (layout/focus/interaction).\n- Effect canonicalization into deterministic command/subscription semantics.\n- IR versioning/explainer tooling plus unit/E2E determinism validation.\n\n## Success Criteria\n1. IR passes are deterministic and idempotent for fixed inputs and configs.\n2. Every normalized artifact is provenance-linked to upstream extraction evidence.\n3. Effect and async semantics map cleanly into deterministic runtime abstractions.\n4. Ingestion-to-IR E2E traces are replayable with stage-level hashes.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:19.821714463Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:22:55.372741464Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["compiler","ir","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:19.821714463Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.3.1","title":"task(opentui-import IR): Design canonical migration IR schema and invariants","description":"Objective: Define canonical IR capturing view tree, state graph, event transitions, effects, style intent, capabilities, and accessibility semantics independent of source syntax.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n1. IR schema is versioned and machine-validated.\\n2. Invariants are explicit (acyclic ownership, deterministic ordering, stable IDs).\\n3. Schema supports provenance links back to source constructs for diagnostics.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:01.555940220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T04:23:42.642835264Z","closed_at":"2026-02-25T04:23:42.642814205Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ir","opentui-import","schema"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:15.022376055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:15.486655395Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:01.555940220Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
