 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.7.8","title":"task(opentui-import UX tests): Unit tests for CLI parsing, config resolution, and explain output stability","description":"Background:\nOperator trust depends on CLI explain outputs remaining stable, accurate, and aligned with evolving galaxy-brain contracts. Parsing/config drift here can invalidate remediation guidance even when core engines are correct.\n\nGoal:\nDeliver exhaustive unit/snapshot/property tests for CLI parsing, config resolution, explain output stability, and L0-L3 card serialization contracts.\n\nWork packages:\n1) CLI + config parser tests:\n- Argument edge cases, invalid combinations, profile overrides, and config precedence rules.\n2) Explain output stability tests:\n- Snapshot guards for report/explain modes including equation/substitution/intuition blocks.\n3) Galaxy-brain serialization tests:\n- Unicode/LaTeX/JSON exports, deterministic content IDs, and non-interference metadata consistency.\n4) Remediation ranking checks:\n- Verify deterministic ranking under equivalent signal sets and consistent rationale clauses.\n5) Logging/replay checks:\n- Structured output schema validation and replay command emission.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Unit + snapshot + property test suite for CLI/explain modules.\n- Fixture matrix across profiles, explain levels, and degraded/normal evidence modes.\n- Diagnostics schema shared with .7.9 E2E operator workflow scripts.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n1) Edge-case arguments and invalid config paths are comprehensively covered.\n2) Explain/report outputs are deterministic for fixed inputs and versioned profiles.\n3) Structured failures emit: command_mode, profile_id, explain_level, card_schema_version, validation_outcome, replay_cmd.\n4) Suite guards upgraded L0-L3 galaxy-brain contracts and blocks drift before .7.9 E2E.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:34:51.589878667Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T23:52:11.726014915Z","source_repo